:"circa 1123","about 1122":"circa 1122","Kilmaurs, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Kilmaurs, Ayrshire, Schotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Schotland"},"en":{"1085–1140":"1085–1140","1094–1124":"1094–1124","1115–1180":"1115–1180","1122–Male":"1122–Deceased","1123–Male":"1123–Deceased","1040–1096":"1040–1096","1044–Female":"1044–Deceased","1080":"1080","about 1096":"about 1096","1044":"1044","1085":"1085","1140":"1140","1096":"1096","1040":"1040","1094":"1094","1180":"1180","1115":"1115","1124":"1124","1123":"1123","1122":"1122","about 1115":"about 1115","about 1123":"about 1123","about 1122":"about 1122","Kilmaurs, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Kilmaurs, Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Cunninghame","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Scottish:  see  Cunningham  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Cunningham","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from the province of Cunningham in Ayrshire, first recorded in 1153 in the form <i>Cunegan</i>, a Celtic name of uncertain origin. The spellings in <i>-ham</i>, first recorded in 1180, and in <i>-ynghame</i>, first recorded in 1227, represent a gradual assimilation to the English placename element <i>-ingham</i>.","I